definition: marked by compactness or crowding together of parts
having a high mass (see mass entry 2 sense 1c) per unit volume (see volume entry 1 sense 2)
examples: Carbon dioxide is a dense gas.
The cake was overly sweet and dense.
was too dense to get the joke

definition: having between any two elements at least one element
examples: The set of rational numbers is dense.

definition: demanding concentration to follow or comprehend
having high or relatively high opacity (see opacity sense 2)
